you get 2013-10-29<p>Tested on 3 different hosts. 
86400 = seconds per day.

I don&#x27;t think this yields the current thread/routine though does it? I think what you are seeing here is closer to express&#x27;:<p><pre><code>  function(req, res, next) {
    console.log(&#x27;before&#x27;);
    next(); // go to the next middleware handler
